  "prompt": "What's a good moveset for Lycanroc in Pokemon Sun and Moon?",
  "response": "Lycanroc has two forms in Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon: Midday Form (Rock) and Midnight Form (Rock). Each has slightly different stats and movesets, so here are optimized movesets for both:\n\n---\n\n### **Lycanroc (Midday Form)**\nMidday Form excels in Speed and Attack, making it a great physical sweeper.\n\n**Recommended Moveset:**\n1. **Stone Edge** (Rock) - High-damage STAB move with a critical hit chance.\n2. **Accelerock** (Rock) - Priority STAB move that hits first, great for finishing off weakened opponents.\n3. **Crunch** (Dark) - Coverage move for Psychic and Ghost types.\n4. **Swords Dance** (Normal) - Boosts Attack sharply, making Lycanroc even more threatening.\n\n**Alternative Moves:**\n- **Brick Break** (Fighting) - For coverage against Steel, Dark, and Normal types.\n- **Fire Fang** (Fire) - Coverage for Grass, Bug, and Steel types.\n\n**Ability:**  \n- **Sand Rush** - Doubles Speed in a sandstorm, making it even faster.\n- **Keen Eye** - Prevents accuracy reduction (useful for moves like Sand Attack).\n\n**Nature:**  \n- **Jolly** (+Speed, -Sp. Atk) - Maximizes Speed to outspeed opponents.\n\n---\n\n### **Lycanroc (Midnight Form)**\nMidnight Form has higher Attack and Defense but lower Speed, making it more suited for a tanky physical attacker.\n\n**Recommended Moveset:**\n1. **Stone Edge** (Rock) - High-damage STAB move.\n2 **Counter** (Fighting) - Reflects physical damage back at the attacker, great for its higher Defense.\n3. **Crunch** (Dark) - Coverage for Psychic and Ghost types.\n4. **Taunt** (Dark) - Prevents opponents from using status moves, disrupting their strategy.\n\n**Alternative Moves:**\n- **Iron Head** (Steel) - Coverage for Fairy and Ice types.\n- **Brick Break** (Fighting) - For Steel, Dark, and Normal types.\n\n**Ability:**  \n- **No Guard** - Ensures all attacks (yours and opponents') never miss.\n\n**Nature:**  \n- **Adamant** (+Attack, -Sp. Atk) - Boosts Attack to deal more damage.\n\n---\n\n### **General Tips:**\n- For Midday Form, focus on its Speed to outspeed opponents and use Accelerock for priority.\n- For Midnight Form, take advantage of its higher Attack and Defense with moves like Counter and Taunt.\n- Both forms benefit from Rock-type STAB moves like Stone Edge.\n\nLet me know if you'd like further details!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
